# AKOS DataOps Discipline

Use this rule whenever authoring or reviewing artefacts that touch
**canonical CSVs**, **Supabase mirrors / FDW projections**,
**`holistika_ops` operational tables**, **Pydantic SSOT modules under
`akos/`**, **mirror sync scripts**, or **observability evidence trails**
covering data quality. Codifies the mechanical layer of
[`DATAOPS_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/DATAOPS_DISCIPLINE.md)
(Wave M P5 mint per D-IH-86-BV).

## When this rule applies

- Mint or modify any canonical CSV under
  `docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/Compliance/canonicals/`.
- Mint or modify any Pydantic SSOT module under `akos/hlk_*_csv.py`.
- Mint or modify any Supabase migration under `supabase/migrations/`.
- Modify mirror sync script `scripts/sync_compliance_mirrors_from_csv.py`
  or add a new mirror-emit step to `compliance_mirror_emit` profile.
- Touch FDW server definitions or `holistika_ops` schemas.

## RULE 1 — Canonical-CSV authoring must satisfy the 7 DataOps dimensions (binding)

Every canonical-CSV mint or schema change must pass the 7 DataOps
dimensions defined in
[`DATAOPS_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/DATAOPS_DISCIPLINE.md)
§2 before commit:

- **DATA-01** FK integrity → `validate_hlk.py` PASS
- **DATA-02** Mirror parity → `compliance_mirror_emit` dry-run clean
- **DATA-03** FDW health → not applicable for non-FDW canonicals;
  mandatory for FDW additions
- **DATA-04** Pipeline freshness → not applicable at mint; applies
  post-mirror-sync
- **DATA-05** Schema drift → Pydantic FIELDNAMES tuple = CSV header
  row = mirror DDL column names
- **DATA-06** Lineage → `PRECEDENCE.md` row added for the new
  canonical
- **DATA-07** DAMA quality metrics → at least one validator covers
  completeness + validity per row

Mechanical enforcement happens via `validate_hlk.py` + paired
`validate_<X>_csv.py` validators + `release-gate.py` integration.

## RULE 2 — Schema changes must coordinate across 3 surfaces (binding)

When a canonical CSV header changes (column add / rename / drop), the
PR or commit must update all three coordinated surfaces atomically:

1. The CSV header row + all data rows.
2. The Pydantic `FIELDNAMES` tuple + `BaseModel` field declarations
   in `akos/hlk_<X>_csv.py`.
3. The Supabase mirror DDL in a new `supabase/migrations/<timestamp>_<desc>.sql`.

A commit that updates one surface without the others creates Schema
Drift (DATA-05) which is a release-gate FAIL per
`akos-holistika-operations.mdc` §"Two-plane model".

## RULE 3 — Mirror parity must hold at release-gate (binding post-promotion)

While DataOps canonical sits at `charter`, mirror parity (DATA-02)
runs at INFO advisory in release-gate. Post-promotion to `active`,
mirror parity becomes a release-gate FAIL — any divergence between
canonical CSV row count and Supabase mirror row count blocks the gate.

The forward promotion gate is defined in
[`DATAOPS_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/DATAOPS_DISCIPLINE.md)
§4 (cadence) + tracked via the paired runbook
`scripts/dataops_quality_check.py` (forward-chartered).

## When this rule does NOT apply

- Test fixtures or ephemeral artifacts under `tests/`.
- One-off migration scripts under `scripts/legacy/` not registered in
  `process_list.csv`.
- Internal scratchwork or debugging notes.

